# JS and CSS Standards

- Keep JavaScript modular; avoid global namespace pollution.
- Use `const`/`let`, avoid `var`, and avoid `console.log` in committed code.
- Enqueue scripts/styles via WordPress APIs; do not hardcode asset tags in templates.
- Localize script data using WordPress helpers instead of inline globals.
- Prefer mobile-first responsive styles and avoid `!important` unless unavoidable.
- Keep CSS maintainable with variables/tokens for repeated values.
- Lazy-load non-critical assets and media where possible.
- Ensure accessibility basics: focus states, keyboard support, and semantic markup.
